President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key positions in his administration. Johnny Collett of Kentucky is nominated to be the Assistant Secretary of Education for Special Education and Rehabilitative Services. Collett is currently the Director of Special Education Outcomes at the Council of Chief State School Officers and has previously served in various roles in special education. John G. Vonglis of New York is nominated to be the Chief Financial Officer of the Department of Energy. Vonglis has experience in finance, private equity, and government, including serving at the Department of Defense. Melissa F. Burnison of Kentucky is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Energy for Congressional and Intergovernmental Affairs. Burnison currently serves as the Director of Federal Programs for the Nuclear Energy Institute, where she develops legislative strategies for nuclear energy programs.